They apologized for not calling me back and refused my pleas to make and acceptance because I had hungry children in my house and even offered to pay extra. They apologized and refused. No empathy during this horrible time. Not a friendly neighborhood restaurant. If you have children please share.

I usually dont have any complains in regards to this Chinese spot but I will never eat from this place again. Usually when I order from here it takes a while for the food to get here and I usually dont mind because the food always comes fresh and delicious. I ordered fried rice with shrimps and broccoli last Sunday and the food came withing ten minutes. As the delivery mad delivered me the food he gave me this look like never before. I thought something was wrong but I didn't really mind nor care because i was just so hungry. 15 minutes as i start to eat my food i start getting really full quickly and immediately my stomach starts to feel uncomfortable. I thought it was a normal stomach ache. When i decided to go to sleep i start to sweat and start to constantly to throw up. I have no doubt that the food was contaminated. I go to the hospital  and they say it was food poisoning. I feel horrible and i am truly disputed at the lack of care in this business. Please do not order from here.
